CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 23, 1953, pg. 36, reads: "New YMCA Branch Officers - These women were elected for the year 1953-54 as officers of the Centre Avenue 'Y' Branch. Left to right: Mrs. Ernest Harshaw, recording secretary; Mrs. Grady Valentine, branch chairman; Mrs. Thomas McCray, first vice president, not shown in picture, and Miss Martha Yowl, corresponding secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Centre Avenue YWCA officers from left: Mrs. Ernest Harshaw holding fur stole, Mrs. Grady Valentine holding document, and Martha Yowl, vertical format
